![][image4]**Web Design, Development, and Migration Agreement** 

The Web Development Agreement (“Agreement”) is entered into on **December 11th** of **2025** (“Effective Date”) by **Praella, LLC** (“Praella”) and **Injectorsdirect.com, Inc**, an **California** company with the principal place of business at **848 Via Esteban, San Luis Obispo, CA 93401, USA** (“Client”). Praella or Client may be referred to as a “Party” or collectively as the “Parties.” 

**SUMMARY** 

With every client that we work with, our utmost goal is the satisfaction of meeting set forth expectations. We aim to maximize the ease of working together. The following Document serves the purpose of Praella understanding the Client's needs. It outlines the scope of work and responsibilities of each party. The Agreement serves to protect the Client and Praella if a disagreement or misunderstanding arises as a reference document. 

Our goal is to provide an easy-to-understand document without confusing or hard-to-understand legal terms. We hope that this Agreement displays the ease of working with us. We look forward to becoming an extension of your team. 

As the extension of your team, we will aim to fulfill your needs and exceed your expectations. However, it is still vital to have expectations written down so that both Parties know what is what. In this Agreement, you will not find any complicated legal language or long paragraphs of unreadable text. We want to ensure that we are aligned. Please take the time and read through it to make sure every requirement you have is within the Agreement. Let us know if you mentioned a requirement on a call or email and the requirement is missing in the Agreement. Addressing missing requirements at this stage will minimize scope creep and reduce the need for Scope of Work adjustments. Lastly, if something is hard to understand, let us know. We are happy to jump on a call and walk you through the Agreement.

**Shopify Store Set-up: Injectors Direct** 

Praella will collaborate with the Client’s internal team to set up the store. Below is an outline of what to expect from Praella. If additional assistance is needed, please notify our team so that we can assist or provide an additional estimate. 

**Payment Processor** 

● Praella will work with the Client to set up the desired payment processor that is 

part of Shopify’s network of accepted and already integrated Payment 

Processors (**Shopify Payments**, Authorize.net, etc.), PayPal, Amazon, Manual 

Payments, etc. 

● Different payment processors are available in different regions of the world. 

Praella will only need the API Login ID and Transaction Key to set up a payment 

processor in most cases. 

● If a processor that the Client wants to use is not part of Shopify’s network or is 

not already integrated with Shopify, the Client and Praella may need permission 

from Shopify to integrate the payment processor. This will also require an 

additional scope of work unless otherwise specified in the Agreement. 

● Praella typically recommends utilizing Shopify Payments, as it tends to have the 

best rates and features. 

● Praella may require the Client's participation in this process. 

**Shipping** 

● Praella will help the Client connect Shopify to any integrated carriers that 

Shopify provides: UPS, USPS, FedEx, etc. 

● Shipping carriers vary by region of the world. 

● If a Client needs a carrier currently not supported by Shopify, a 3rd party or an 

app might be needed. 

● Out of the box, Shopify offers shipping conditions like shipping zones, weights, 

free shipping, rates, restrictions, etc.

**Data Migration** 

Praella will work with the Client to migrate data from the Client’s current **Woocommerce** instance over to the new **Shopify Plus** instance. The scope only includes automated migration work; if manual migration work is needed, it may require an additional scope. 

The reflective scope defined in this Agreement assumes that the Client will provide Praella with access to the **Woocommerce** database. It is also assumed that the database can be accessed via API. If data needs to be migrated through a data dump or CSV-based files, the additional scope may need to be added to this Agreement or a Scope Amendment. 

The reflective scope defined in this Agreement assumes that Praella will not need to clean up data to migrate the data successfully. If data clean-up or manipulation is needed, an additional scope may need to be added to the Agreement or a Scope Amendment. 

If the Client has to provide iterations of data or batches of data, this, too, may result in additional scope added to the Agreement or a Scope Amendment.

This migration stage is done right before launch to bring the data up to date as 

much as possible. Stage 2 of the migration process is typically a much smaller 

migration stage compared to Stage 1\. 

● **Stage 3: Post-Launch Gap Migration** 

This migration stage is executed right after launch to update any data points that 

might be stragglers.

**On-Site Search Engine Optimization and 301 Redirects** 

Praella will plan and execute the creation of the new website and the migration of the data utilizing Shopify’s native SEO tools. Praella will also leverage Search Console and Google Analytics if the Client has the two available. 

**● 301 Audit** 

**○** Creating 301 redirects contributes to preserving or improving organic 

traffic or re-directing any external links that might send traffic to the 

Client’s website. 

○ Praella will execute an initial 301 redirect audit of the Client's website. 

Praella will leverage the Client’s Search Console and Google Analytics to 

plan the 301 redirects. 

○ Praella may not be able to account for all possible 301s needed; however, 

Praella will leverage the 3rd party tools that it has available to mitigate any 

unaccounted 301s. 

● **Mapping and Implementation of 301 Redirects** 

○ Based on the audit and planning, Praella will map links and 301s directly 

based on the URL structure of **Woocommerce**. The URLs will then be 

mapped over to **Shopify Plus** based on **Shopify Plus’** URL structure. 

This is the process taken to minimize and mitigate SEO degradation. 

Praella will utilize 3rd party tools like Search Console, Screaming Frog, 

Transporter, or a similar app (paid Shopify app the Client will need to 

add), and SEO scanners to analyze and audit the 301s post-launch.
